{
  "stem": "9701.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And the reason for the decrease of the, of the number of Jewish children was because their families were fortunate enough to be able to leave Germany.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was at that time probably relatively easy to leave Germany, because the Nazis wanted to get rid of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "It was more difficult to find a country that would receive you and someone in that country to sponsor you.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "My parents had also tried desperately to find relatives somewhere, somehow, who could sponsor us and so that we could leave.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But we had not been successful.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And as the number of Jewish children decreased in that school, the anti-Semitism seemed to increase.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And as much as the Christian children no longer talked to me, or if they did talk to me, they'd call me a dirty Jew, or some other choice names.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Recess was the loneliest time of the day, because no one would talk to me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And no one would play with me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And I also had the great misfortune the last two and a half years that I was in that school to have had a math teacher who was an SS man.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "The SS were the Nazi elite, the storm troopers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And he came to school almost daily, wearing his black SS uniform and knee-high black boots.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And in his right boot, he always carried a revolver.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And whenever he asked me a question, he wou-- and he asked me lots of questions-- he would either have his hand at the revolved-- on the revolver, or a couple times, he actually pointed it at me.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And no matter what my answers were, whether they were right or wrong, he would ridicule me in front of my classmates and say, that's a Jewish answer.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
